measurements.description:
Six flowers and one bud on one 70-cm arching inflorescence; 
	dorsal sepal arching forward, yellow heavily overlaid dark red, veins and margins very dark; 
	lateral sepals slightly reflexed, yellow heavily overlaid dark red except centrally on each side of very dark central vein;
	petals reflexed, some curling at side margins, yellow overlaid dark red, darker mid-rib, distal edges yellow;
	lip white, purple markings, callus white, purple markings, side-lobes yellow, purple markings; 
	column arched, yellow, purple spotting;
	substance firm; texture matte.
	AD is awarded for maintaining the erythraeum species charm while introducing intense color from a standard cymbidium.
	Hybridizer Santa Barbara Orchid Estate.
